Hindustan Petroleum Sells Naphtha Cargoes to Cargill, PetroChina

-- B y   P r a t i s h   N a r a y a n a n
-- 
2011-05-12T06:31:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-12/hindustan-petroleum-sells-naphtha-cargoes-to-cargill-petrochina.html
Hindustan Petroleum Corp.,  India ’s
third-largest state refiner, sold as much as 60,000 metric tons
of naphtha to Cargill Inc. and PetroChina Co., according to two
traders who participate in the market.  Details of the refiner’s sale are as follow:  Hindustan Petroleum operates two refineries, one in Mumbai
on the west coast of India and another in Visakhapatnam on the
east coast.  To contact the reporter on this story:
